I intentionally avoided this because i don't want the CTime testing testing a different binary than the users are using in practice.

As an option, I suppose I don't care... however: more options means that the CI needs to test that that combination compiles, and this (useless?) configuration option might not be worth the ci overhead.

@luke-jr Those aren't used at runtime, no _VERIFY macro is. They are purely test-only instrumentation See util.h.
